WEBVTT

00:10.010 --> 00:13.680
["MMMBop" playing]

00:55.680 --> 00:57.974
["MMMBop" continues playing]

01:04.105 --> 01:06.900
[Naomi] So, now on to final business.

01:06.983 --> 01:10.028
-Anyone?
-Yeah, I actually have some news to share.

01:10.111 --> 01:13.698
Yeah, the book that Ethan Turner and I
have been working on

01:13.782 --> 01:15.158
is ready for prime time.

01:15.241 --> 01:17.577
-We just broke it wide open...
-[shouts] Wait!

01:17.660 --> 01:19.454
I am so sorry to interrupt.

01:19.537 --> 01:20.789
Good morning, Patel.

01:20.872 --> 01:22.832
I love your beret.

01:22.916 --> 01:27.212
Thanks. Anyway, I just got off the phone
with Anne Michael at Random.

01:27.295 --> 01:32.967
They are bidding mid-seven figures
for Patty Ho's<i> Wolf Trials</i> series!

01:33.051 --> 01:34.969
Oh, God, that's awesome!

01:35.053 --> 01:37.138
[all howl]

01:41.684 --> 01:43.686
I don't know what we're doing. Why--

01:43.770 --> 01:46.689
Get your hands out of my face, Patel!
Why are you howling?

01:46.773 --> 01:48.233
That's my book,<i> Wolf Trials.</i>

01:48.316 --> 01:51.111
The book Ethan Turner and I
were working on,<i> Wolf Trials.</i>

01:51.194 --> 01:52.987
What are you talking about?

01:53.530 --> 01:57.826
<i>Wolf Trials!</i> I was gonna just announce it
right now to all you guys!

01:58.409 --> 02:00.620
-Are you joking?
-No, I'm not joking!

02:00.703 --> 02:01.704
Are you joking?

02:01.788 --> 02:03.665
Are you joking? I'm not joking.

02:03.748 --> 02:07.877
Max,<i> Wolf Trials</i> has been in the works
for at least a year.

02:08.837 --> 02:09.963
That...

02:12.257 --> 02:13.508
I got it.

02:14.384 --> 02:17.262
I'm getting punked.
You guys are punking me.

02:17.345 --> 02:19.305
No one's punking anyone.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.891
I mean, we discuss it
at every single meeting.

02:21.975 --> 02:24.185
You even contributed some ideas.

02:27.897 --> 02:30.942
["MMMBop" playing slow and distorted]

02:44.914 --> 02:49.794
No one has ever thought
to put a wolf on trial.

02:49.878 --> 02:52.130
[Naomi] And what do you think, Max?

02:52.213 --> 02:55.633
I think it should end with a...
with a big courtroom scene.

03:14.402 --> 03:17.739
I think you might be a little distracted
on the personal front.

03:18.531 --> 03:20.116
I punked you guys.

03:21.284 --> 03:22.577
I punked you, that was a...

03:23.828 --> 03:25.705
the reverse punk, so...

03:26.331 --> 03:28.041
I pulled a switch on you.

03:29.667 --> 03:31.002
I reversed it.

03:33.254 --> 03:35.173
[soft rock song playing]

03:43.806 --> 03:44.974
[sighs]

03:45.475 --> 03:48.061
A lot of people
find their 40th birthdays challenging.

03:48.645 --> 03:52.398
-Please don't try to make this about that.
-What do you think it's about?

03:52.482 --> 03:54.817
Why don't you tell me?
You're the professional.

03:55.652 --> 03:57.737
-Your 40th birthday.
-[scoffs]

03:57.820 --> 04:00.156
Well, there's some
circular reasoning for you.

04:00.240 --> 04:02.617
I have no fear of getting older.

04:02.700 --> 04:05.286
It's just that all the choices disappear.

04:05.370 --> 04:07.872
Everything's been decided for me.

04:07.956 --> 04:10.667
I mean, I'm just locked into my life.

04:10.750 --> 04:14.254
Who I'm married to, who my children are,
what I do for a living,

04:14.337 --> 04:17.090
it's all done, all the doors are closed.

04:17.173 --> 04:20.593
There's only one door I haven't
walked through and I'm not eager to.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.011
So you feel trapped?

04:22.637 --> 04:24.514
What? No.

04:24.597 --> 04:25.974
I love my life.

04:26.057 --> 04:29.352
I just sometimes wonder what would happen
if it was blown to smithereens

04:29.435 --> 04:31.145
and I got to start all over again.

04:31.729 --> 04:32.647
Is that crazy?

04:32.730 --> 04:35.149
People blow up their lives all the time.

04:35.233 --> 04:37.986
Right. It's not like
my family's gonna disappear.

04:38.069 --> 04:42.407
I'm not gonna wake up one morning and find
out that Ethan is single, for example.

04:42.490 --> 04:44.450
That's not the main thing
I'm thinking about.

04:44.826 --> 04:46.703
You bring that up in every session.

04:47.245 --> 04:48.746
Well, someone's keeping score.

04:48.830 --> 04:50.415
I'm just observing a pattern.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.292
And I'm observing a pattern, too.

04:52.375 --> 04:54.544
Of hostile score-keeping.

04:56.337 --> 04:57.714
[Ethan squeals]

04:58.673 --> 04:59.882
[Nick yells]

05:00.508 --> 05:01.384
[Ethan squeals]

05:01.467 --> 05:02.969
[Nick yells]

05:04.262 --> 05:05.471
[Ethan squeals]

05:05.555 --> 05:07.015
[Nick screams]

05:07.724 --> 05:08.766
[Ethan squeals]

05:08.850 --> 05:10.101
[cell phone rings]

05:10.184 --> 05:11.227
[Nick groans]

05:11.811 --> 05:12.895
[Nick] Hold on one second.

05:18.568 --> 05:19.444
Hello.

05:19.527 --> 05:20.486
Hey.

05:20.570 --> 05:22.155
<i>Hey. Welcome home, mon!</i>

05:22.238 --> 05:24.574
I'm still on the plane. Um...

05:25.867 --> 05:27.493
I'm gonna call Ethan.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.829
He's right here, mon.
You want to talk to him, mon?

05:29.912 --> 05:31.539
No, I don't want to do that.

05:31.622 --> 05:34.542
I don't want him to even know
that this is me.

05:34.625 --> 05:36.711
Can you take a few steps away from him?

05:37.253 --> 05:38.421
Uh, alright.

05:39.297 --> 05:41.174
You look so hot in those goggles, bro.

05:41.591 --> 05:43.301
<i>I just wanted to let you know</i>

05:43.384 --> 05:46.137
that I am gonna tell Ethan what happened.

05:46.220 --> 05:48.181
<i>Unless you already have.</i>

05:48.264 --> 05:51.100
No. I did not.
Of course I wouldn't tell him. Right?

05:51.184 --> 05:54.228
There was nothing serious about it.
Isn't that what you said?

05:54.312 --> 05:57.899
Just one person fucking the other person's
dick off for eight hours.

05:57.982 --> 06:01.736
We're not gonna get back into this.
We're not gonna go down that road, okay?

06:01.819 --> 06:02.820
-Nick, look.
-No.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.113
Nick...

06:04.197 --> 06:05.406
[groans]

06:05.490 --> 06:08.201
<i>I need to tell Ethan.</i>
<i>I think it's the right thing to do.</i>

06:08.743 --> 06:10.953
Don't fucking say anything, okay?

06:11.037 --> 06:13.790
I've been through this before
and nothing good comes from it.

06:14.373 --> 06:16.584
I can't live with this anymore, I can't.

06:16.667 --> 06:18.878
I feel like I'm gonna throw up
all the time.

06:19.462 --> 06:20.630
Please don't, okay?

06:20.713 --> 06:23.925
Please don't say anything.
We have Sam's party coming up.

06:24.008 --> 06:27.386
I don't think we're going to that.
I'm gonna tell him as soon as I land.

06:27.470 --> 06:28.971
-Nick, look...
-Lisa...

06:29.055 --> 06:30.014
<i>Bye.</i>

06:30.848 --> 06:32.600
[Nick laughs] What?

06:32.683 --> 06:35.728
I'm gonna even return balls like that.
Watch this shit.

06:35.812 --> 06:37.522
-You don't even understand.
-Oh...

06:38.106 --> 06:39.816
[Ethan] Ready for some service?

06:39.899 --> 06:41.359
[cell phone rings]

06:42.360 --> 06:43.528
I'm gonna, um...

06:43.903 --> 06:46.155
-I'm just gonna grab some water, I think.
-Yeah.

06:46.239 --> 06:48.491
-I'm feeling, uh...
-Let me take this real quick.

06:48.574 --> 06:50.660
Okay. I just don't know if my water is--

06:50.743 --> 06:53.704
You're super in the way. Super in the way.
[chuckles]

06:54.122 --> 06:55.081
There we go.

06:55.164 --> 06:58.334
Haha! [in Caribbean accent] Ya, mon!
Have you landed, mon?

06:59.210 --> 07:01.671
Are you gonna be home when I get there?

07:01.754 --> 07:04.632
Ya, mon,
I'm planning on being home there

07:04.715 --> 07:07.760
and that you and I
are gonna go to the party together.

07:07.927 --> 07:09.804
<i>Uh, yeah, listen, um...</i>

07:11.180 --> 07:14.308
We need to talk before we go to Sam's.

07:14.392 --> 07:16.018
<i>We need to talk.</i>

07:16.686 --> 07:18.729
-What about?
<i>-It's better in person.</i>

07:19.063 --> 07:20.815
Are you okay? Did something happen?

07:20.898 --> 07:22.108
No, um...

07:24.110 --> 07:27.405
-You know, we'll talk soon.
-No, we can talk now. Lisa, please.

07:27.488 --> 07:29.031
<i>-Uh, I mean...</i>
<i>-</i>I'm...

07:29.115 --> 07:30.616
We'll talk later, okay?

07:30.700 --> 07:31.742
<i>Okay, bye.</i>

07:41.169 --> 07:43.129
-Uh, you good?
-Yeah.

07:47.341 --> 07:48.176
I'm good.

07:48.885 --> 07:51.095
[Sam] The gala,
I am not looking forward to it.

07:51.179 --> 07:52.472
-Hey, Sam.
-Hi.

07:52.555 --> 07:55.224
Can I just have her for just a second?
Thanks so much.

07:55.308 --> 07:57.894
I'm so sorry.
I will be right back, please excuse me.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.938
-What are you doing here?
-I think Lisa knows about us.

08:01.522 --> 08:02.607
What? How?

08:02.690 --> 08:06.152
She just called me from the runway
and said we need to talk in person.

08:06.235 --> 08:08.696
Nothing good ever happens
when a wife says that.

08:08.779 --> 08:11.032
Listen,
I am going to tell Lisa everything.

08:11.115 --> 08:12.116
-No.
-Yes.

08:12.200 --> 08:13.409
-No, you are not.
-Yes.

08:13.493 --> 08:16.996
-Yes, I am, Sam. I am, Sam.
-No, you're not. No!

08:17.079 --> 08:19.540
Stop! I am Sam
and you are not telling her anything!

08:19.624 --> 08:21.751
I'm going to tell her.
I wanted you to know.

08:21.834 --> 08:25.796
This is a decision that we make together
and I forbid you from saying a word.

08:26.380 --> 08:29.217
There's nothing to say, anyway.
We're done, remember?

08:29.300 --> 08:30.301
I know that.

08:30.384 --> 08:33.679
You don't get to blow up my marriage
and my children's lives

08:33.763 --> 08:35.306
to alleviate your conscience.

08:35.389 --> 08:38.518
If you feel better, I will tell her
I had the affair with someone else.

08:38.601 --> 08:40.770
Please! She'll figure out you're lying
within ten seconds.

08:40.853 --> 08:41.938
No, she won't.

08:42.021 --> 08:42.939
Listen.

08:43.856 --> 08:48.402
I wish it were as easy as telling Lisa
and moving on, but it isn't.

08:50.279 --> 08:53.783
It will change your marriage irrevocably
and mine, too.

08:54.158 --> 08:57.328
Obviously, but believe me,
I've given this a lot of thought.

08:57.411 --> 08:58.829
It's over.

08:58.913 --> 09:00.289
We're done.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.457
That's what matters.

09:04.085 --> 09:05.711
Please don't blow up my life.

09:05.795 --> 09:06.671
Please.

09:06.754 --> 09:09.715
Listen to me. Your kids are coming, okay.

09:11.175 --> 09:12.301
Mommy!

09:12.385 --> 09:13.636
-Hey!
-Mommy!

09:13.719 --> 09:15.388
Hello, my loves!

09:15.471 --> 09:17.098
-Hello!
-What's up, guys?

09:17.181 --> 09:19.141
Are you coming to karate with us?

09:19.225 --> 09:21.686
Are you talking about...
[makes high-pitched noises]

09:21.769 --> 09:24.105
I'm sorry, I can't guys. I wish I could.

09:24.188 --> 09:26.148
Let's go. Bye-bye, Ethan.

09:26.232 --> 09:28.317
-Bye-bye.
-[Sam] Bye-bye.

09:32.697 --> 09:34.740
[Sam] We'll give those ones
to the squirrels.

09:41.038 --> 09:44.542
[pilot] <i>Hi, folks. I have some bad news</i>
<i>from Ground Control.</i>

09:44.625 --> 09:47.712
<i>A storm system is over the Chesapeake,</i>
<i>so we have to wait it out.</i>

09:47.795 --> 09:49.964
<i>Shouldn't be much more</i>
<i>than a half hour.</i>

09:50.047 --> 09:52.049
<i>So we're gonna keep you here on the plane.</i>

09:52.133 --> 09:53.467
[passengers groan]

09:53.551 --> 09:54.468
-Whoo!
-Yeah!

09:54.552 --> 09:56.971
Okay, stop. Stop.

09:57.513 --> 09:59.432
[pilot] <i>Hello again from the flight deck.</i>

09:59.515 --> 10:02.143
<i>That storm system is lingering a bit.</i>

10:02.226 --> 10:04.186
<i>But it shouldn't be more than an hour.</i>

10:04.270 --> 10:05.396
[passengers groan louder]

10:05.479 --> 10:08.482
<i>We're gonna hand out</i>
<i>complimentary champagne</i>

10:08.566 --> 10:10.067
<i>to thank you for your patience.</i>

10:10.151 --> 10:11.736
[cheering]

10:11.819 --> 10:13.529
[sighs]

10:16.365 --> 10:18.117
<i>Hello, folks, me again.</i>

10:18.200 --> 10:20.620
<i>Traffic patterns are backed up all over,</i>

10:20.703 --> 10:22.872
<i>so we may be diverted to Newark.</i>

10:24.415 --> 10:26.292
<i>We'll have more information in an hour.</i>

10:26.375 --> 10:28.085
I don't wanna go to this party.

10:28.169 --> 10:31.756
What? A party with our college friends
and Ethan Turner doesn't wanna go?

10:31.839 --> 10:35.217
I just...
I want to be at home to meet Lisa.

10:35.301 --> 10:38.054
You know what I was thinking? Centaurs.

10:38.763 --> 10:40.056
-What?
-Your next book.

10:40.139 --> 10:41.891
Your next book after<i> Wolf Trials.</i>

10:41.974 --> 10:43.976
Centaurs, half-man, half-horse.

10:44.060 --> 10:46.020
Super buff, long hair,

10:46.103 --> 10:48.689
great posture, kind of forest-dwelling.

10:48.773 --> 10:51.108
-It'd be super cool.
-What the fuck are you talking about?

10:51.192 --> 10:55.071
You could just replace the word "werewolf"
for "centaur" in the document.

10:55.154 --> 10:57.615
Maybe we should probably see
how<i> Wolf Trials</i> does first.

10:57.698 --> 11:00.910
Yeah, although, you know,
never too soon to get on that next idea

11:00.993 --> 11:03.913
or even replace the current idea
with the new one.

11:03.996 --> 11:06.040
Max, I'm sorry, I just...

11:06.123 --> 11:08.209
I just finished a 400-page draft

11:08.292 --> 11:10.878
so I'm a little fucking tapped out
right now.

11:10.961 --> 11:12.463
You wrote 400 pages?

11:12.546 --> 11:14.673
-Yeah, it's a fucking book.
-Right.

11:16.300 --> 11:18.427
Are you mad?
Because you're swearing a lot.

11:18.511 --> 11:20.763
I just wanna fucking go home
and meet with Lisa.

11:20.846 --> 11:23.933
-That's all I wanna fucking do.
-Alright. F-word. Jeez!

11:24.016 --> 11:26.310
-Can we just get on the train, please?
-Like we're in a saloon.

11:46.747 --> 11:48.916
Haha! Va-va-voom!

11:49.959 --> 11:51.544
I want to cancel the party.

11:51.961 --> 11:53.879
