to take a nap.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.871
Does it ever creep you out
living in this house?

12:27.246 --> 12:30.666
Mmm... no, because I have nothing to hide.

12:32.126 --> 12:36.005
It did creep me out a little bit when that
bear threw the chair through the window.

12:37.631 --> 12:43.012
That means that he was inside the house
and wanted to get the hell out.

12:43.095 --> 12:46.056
Whenever you see me zoning out,
I'm thinking about that bear

12:46.140 --> 12:47.975
running around inside our house.

12:48.058 --> 12:49.143
Creepy.

12:50.060 --> 12:51.437
Doesn't make sense.

12:51.520 --> 12:54.690
-A bear doesn't have opposable thumbs.
-Stop talking about this bear thing.

12:55.357 --> 12:59.278
-Do you know where Pearl and Marianne are?
-No, I think they're outside playing.

12:59.904 --> 13:01.238
[Sam] Where?

13:01.822 --> 13:03.157
Now hit the brake.

13:03.699 --> 13:06.035
-Which one is the brake?
-The one on the left.

13:07.953 --> 13:09.288
Now put it in park.

13:11.248 --> 13:13.792
-Nice job.
-Can I have more Red Bull now?

13:14.335 --> 13:15.461
You bet.

13:15.544 --> 13:16.754
[Sam] Hi.

13:17.213 --> 13:18.797
Thank you so much for coming.

13:18.881 --> 13:19.757
Hello!

13:19.840 --> 13:21.884
-I'm old.
