15:18.584 --> 15:20.419
-Wow.
-Lisa, look.

15:21.128 --> 15:22.713
-Lisa, look.
-It's beautiful.

15:23.380 --> 15:25.841
-Lisa, look.
-I see, yeah. It's really lovely.

15:25.925 --> 15:28.928
I, like, still can't even believe it.
It's like...

15:29.011 --> 15:30.012
[makes a bleating noise]

15:30.095 --> 15:30.971
Like...

15:31.055 --> 15:31.889
[bleats]

15:31.972 --> 15:33.933
-Yeah.
-Holy moly. Who is this?

15:34.016 --> 15:35.434
What is that?

15:35.517 --> 15:38.312
Oh. Uh, this is my fiancée, Dustry.

15:38.395 --> 15:40.189
We're engaged to be married.

15:40.272 --> 15:42.608
-Well, congratulations.
-I know, I was like...

15:42.691 --> 15:43.567
[bleats]

15:43.651 --> 15:44.526
Just like...

15:44.610 --> 15:45.444
[bleats]

15:45.527 --> 15:47.821
-Like...
-[Nick] Yeah, I was, too.

15:47.905 --> 15:50.616
-Bear, you're so cute!
-You're cute, Bug.

15:50.699 --> 15:52.701
I want to show you these bouquets.

15:52.785 --> 15:53.827
What for?

15:53.911 --> 15:55.162
For our wedding.

15:55.245 --> 15:56.789
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

16:00.793 --> 16:03.796
-What is going on with those two?
-I have no idea.

16:03.879 --> 16:05.756
Oh, how were the Caymans?

16:06.048 --> 16:07.007
[sighs]

16:07.675 --> 16:08.926
Terrible.

16:12.930 --> 16:14.556
-I'll take-- Yeah. Mm-hmm.
-Yeah.

16:20.396 --> 16:21.981
[whispers] You're right. She knows.

16:22.064 --> 16:25.234
Ladies and gentlemen,
grab your coats and come on outside

16:25.317 --> 16:27.903
for a special presentation.

16:28.654 --> 16:32.324
Uh, as you all know, my wife, Samantha,

16:32.408 --> 16:34.118
loves a good surprise.

16:34.201 --> 16:37.037
Oh, no. What have you done?

16:37.121 --> 16:39.289
Which is why your friends and I

16:39.373 --> 16:43.002
have organized a very special...

16:43.085 --> 16:45.129
[Dash and Pearl] Night of surprises!

16:45.212 --> 16:46.672
[guests gasp]

16:47.798 --> 16:49.049
I helped with the sign!

16:49.133 --> 16:51.051
It's beautiful, I love it.

16:51.135 --> 16:53.303
[Jon] For my first surprise,

16:53.387 --> 16:56.140
and don't worry, honey,
because I've got a few,

16:56.223 --> 16:59.435
let me introduce Nils Michelson.

16:59.518 --> 17:02.146
Come over here, everybody,
gather round over here.

17:02.229 --> 17:03.856
[dramatic fanfare music]

17:03.939 --> 17:05.065
[Jon] Right over here.

17:05.816 --> 17:09.862
Can anyone tell me what the most
dangerous weapon in the world is?

17:09.945 --> 17:11.947
-[Ethan] Machine gun?
-[Max] Two machine guns?

17:12.031 --> 17:13.574
-No.
-Nuclear weapons.

17:13.657 --> 17:14.825
-That's good.
-Bomb.

17:14.908 --> 17:17.036
-It's a bow and arrow.
-[Max] He's not right.

17:17.119 --> 17:19.246
That's not right.
A nuclear weapon would...

17:19.329 --> 17:21.457
[Nils] Now we all know it's bow and arrow,

17:21.540 --> 17:22.916
let's start the show.

17:23.584 --> 17:25.044
[dramatic music plays]

17:26.378 --> 17:27.254
[guests gasp]

17:29.798 --> 17:30.841
[guests] Oh!

17:36.472 --> 17:38.015
[Max] Wow, look at that!

17:40.184 --> 17:41.727
Oh!

17:44.730 --> 17:46.190
[panicked chatter]

17:54.782 --> 17:56.033
[guests applaud]

17:56.116 --> 17:59.703
Alright, for my next surprise,
let's all go into the dining room.

17:59.787 --> 18:02.164
-[Ethan] That's us. We gotta go!
-[Nils] I need to get paid.

18:02.247 --> 18:05.209
-[Ethan] Friend group, let's go.
-[Marianne] Friend group.

18:05.292 --> 18:07.836
So let's just run lines one more time
from the top.

18:07.920 --> 18:10.422
-I'm good, I'll just read it.
-We said no scripts.

18:10.506 --> 18:13.926
-We said we're gonna do this off book.
-Are we sure we want do this?

18:14.009 --> 18:17.721
Of course we want to do this! This is
<i>Monica Lewinsky, The Musical,</i> guys.

18:17.805 --> 18:20.599
-That's right.
-That's why you got a stain on the jacket.

18:20.682 --> 18:21.517
Sorry!

18:21.600 --> 18:24.186
This is one of the surprises
in the Night of Surprises.

18:24.269 --> 18:26.146
We gotta do it or else it's just a night.

18:26.230 --> 18:30.067
In my experience, a performance
has to answer two fundamental questions.

18:30.150 --> 18:34.363
-Why here, why now?
-Exactly, and this answers none of them.

18:34.446 --> 18:36.031
I think Marianne's right.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.576
This is a very elegant party.
I think it could be disrespectful.

18:39.660 --> 18:40.494
Agreed.

18:40.577 --> 18:43.705
[as Bill Clinton] I think it's gonna be
a lot of fun for everybody involved.

18:43.789 --> 18:46.792
I don't want to play Linda Tripp.
I always play Linda Tripp.

18:46.875 --> 18:49.044
I never get to play the good characters.

18:49.128 --> 18:52.631
Come on, the play is not terrible.
We're doing this for Sam. It's sweet.

18:52.714 --> 18:54.299
-The play's really good.
-Yes!

18:54.383 --> 18:58.887
It seems irrelevant and depressing,
given the way things turned out.

18:58.971 --> 19:03.392
Well, I think it's a great opportunity
for people to relive my legacy.

19:03.976 --> 19:06.562
[as Obama] I've gotta tell you,
Bill, I think it's a bad idea.

19:06.645 --> 19:09.398
It does not paint you in a good light.

19:09.481 --> 19:11.859
[as Trump] And I wanna say
that both of you are stupid,

19:11.942 --> 19:15.112
your wife and your daughter together,
equal a six, okay?

19:15.195 --> 19:17.406
She's a three, she's a two, they're a six.

19:17.489 --> 19:18.866
[as Clinton] That's faulty math.

19:18.949 --> 19:21.243
-Stop it!
-Stop! Stop doing the thing!

19:21.326 --> 19:22.536
-Stop!
-It's annoying.

19:22.619 --> 19:27.332
Guys, listen. Do you remember our
performance at the Leverett Old Library?

19:27.416 --> 19:28.250
Okay?

19:28.333 --> 19:32.254
The students complained because the
laughter was so loud nobody could study.

19:32.337 --> 19:34.173
Do you remember that? That laughter?

19:34.256 --> 19:37.134
That's what we gotta get back to.
That's how good this is!

19:37.217 --> 19:39.303
I don't know,
the second you said students,

19:39.386 --> 19:41.013
it reminded me that was 20 years ago.

19:41.096 --> 19:42.431
Maybe it doesn't hold up.

19:42.514 --> 19:44.850
Max, the play sucks.

19:44.933 --> 19:46.143
You suck, Marianne!

19:46.226 --> 19:48.478
-You know what else sucks? Your play.
-Don't.

19:48.562 --> 19:52.191
That stupid gender-bending
<i>Streetcar Named Desire</i> play.

19:52.274 --> 19:54.234
-That was a disaster.
-[Ethan] Max...

19:54.818 --> 19:55.903
[Nick] Ooh.

19:56.361 --> 19:57.613
I'm sorry, that...

19:58.113 --> 20:00.490
I didn't mean that.
I love you, Marianne. I'm sorry.

20:00.574 --> 20:03.660
I get carried away when I put on the wig
and I become Kenneth Starr

20:03.744 --> 20:06.705
and I just attack
without provocation or evidence.

20:06.788 --> 20:09.791
-I get a little... "Monica-rena."
-["Macarena" plays]

20:09.875 --> 20:11.793
-Do you hear the "Monica-rena"?
-Yes. Max...

20:11.877 --> 20:14.630
That's the show! It's started.
It's out of our hands.

20:14.713 --> 20:15.923
We gotta finish the show.

20:16.006 --> 20:19.218
And people are gonna love it, okay?
Here we go, off-book!

20:19.676 --> 20:21.970
-I don't want to do this.
-I know, man, I know.

20:22.054 --> 20:24.181
I look like a Hasidic Garth.

20:48.288 --> 20:49.498
Good evening.

20:49.998 --> 20:53.335
I am Kenneth Starr
and I request your attention.

20:53.835 --> 20:55.128
Guys, hands on hips.

20:55.212 --> 20:56.588
Turn off the music.

20:57.881 --> 21:00.968
-I thought you wanted me to--
-[Ethan] Stop the music.

21:01.051 --> 21:02.886
Turn off the music.

21:02.970 --> 21:05.931
-Okay. This is all part of the thing.
-[Max stammers]

21:08.725 --> 21:12.646
Hey, um... As some of Sam's
closest friends,

21:12.729 --> 21:14.856
we'd like to say...

21:20.946 --> 21:24.616
-[whispers] Take it easy, Counselor.
-Gotta think it through. We had a plan--

21:24.700 --> 21:26.702
Shut the fuck up.
<i>Streetcar</i> was awesome.

21:26.785 --> 21:28.245
It was shit and this is shit.

21:28.328 --> 21:30.580
-[indistinct whispers]
-Shh.

21:32.582 --> 21:39.172
♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪

21:39.256 --> 21:44.136
-♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪
-No, no, no!

21:44.219 --> 21:46.263
No. We haven't even had dinner yet.

21:46.346 --> 21:48.890
Hold on. We haven't had dinner.

21:48.974 --> 21:51.727
We haven't... It's too soon.
[nervous chuckle]

21:52.227 --> 21:53.854
Sorry, my bad, I guess. Uh...

21:54.021 --> 21:55.731
-I guess we should eat...
-Yeah.

21:55.814 --> 21:57.733
-And then we'll...
-[Ethan] Sorry about that.

22:00.986 --> 22:02.112
What's happening?

22:02.195 --> 22:05.240
Forget it, we're not doing it.
You guys win.

22:07.284 --> 22:08.702
Well, that was great!

22:08.785 --> 22:10.620
Thank you guys so much!

22:11.079 --> 22:12.622
Hey, everybody, let's eat.

22:12.706 --> 22:15.334
-Happy birthday, Sam.
-Thank you. Thank you.

22:15.459 --> 22:17.210
-That was a roller coaster.
-It was.

22:30.057 --> 22:32.726
-Hi. Can I talk to you?
-What's up?

22:33.310 --> 22:34.561
-[angrily] Ethan!
-Yeah?

22:34.644 --> 22:37.397
-Hi. Can you come over here?
-Sure, honey.

22:40.567 --> 22:41.985
What's up?

22:42.402 --> 22:43.487
Anastasia.

22:43.570 --> 22:45.572
I didn't know she was invited tonight.

22:45.655 --> 22:48.450
She wasn't.
I found her outside by the pool.

22:49.659 --> 22:50.535
Okay.

22:51.078 --> 22:52.496
This is my rabbit.

22:52.579 --> 22:56.208
Not the impostor one that you tried
to pass off on me, whom I love now, too.

22:57.834 --> 23:00.378
I don't know what this is.
I'm going back to the party.

23:00.462 --> 23:02.172
Sam, get over here now.

23:03.799 --> 23:05.759
You were supposed
to take Anastasia to the vet,

23:05.842 --> 23:09.221
yet she ended up here, 50 miles away
in Connecticut, in Sam's house,

23:09.304 --> 23:11.598
which means
you two are still having an affair.

23:11.681 --> 23:14.017
-[laughs nervously]
-Hang on, how does she know about us?

23:14.101 --> 23:17.729
Sam, when you told me that it was over,
I believed you. And I was so relieved.

23:17.813 --> 23:19.689
How long have you known about us?

23:19.773 --> 23:22.442
Why do you care about this so much?
This is not your life.

23:22.526 --> 23:24.986
Why do I care so much?
It's because I love you guys.

23:25.946 --> 23:26.905
You're my family.

23:26.988 --> 23:30.534
No! I have a family
and they are sitting right over there.

23:31.118 --> 23:33.328
Oh, my God, Sam, you know what I mean.

23:33.411 --> 23:36.289
She knows everything?
Why did you tell her?

23:36.998 --> 23:40.001
I am a human being.
I need someone to talk to.

23:40.085 --> 23:41.753
Okay, I have to tell Lisa, okay?

23:41.837 --> 23:44.631
She already knows,
and apparently everybody else does too,

23:44.714 --> 23:47.134
and it'll make it better
if I get to her first.

23:47.217 --> 23:49.010
-You can't.
-I think you should.

23:49.094 --> 23:51.221
-Thank you, Marianne.
-No, please.

23:51.304 --> 23:54.015
Please, Ethan, please don't,
it's my birthday.

23:55.684 --> 23:58.019
I'm gonna take Anastasia to the bedroom

23:58.103 --> 23:59.896
where she will eat most of your shoes.

24:02.858 --> 24:04.818
Hey, is everything okay?

24:04.901 --> 24:07.571
So many secrets. Poisonous secrets.

24:13.535 --> 24:14.703
-Lisa.
-Yes?

24:14.786 --> 24:17.372
-Can we go for just a second, have a word?
-Yeah.

24:17.455 --> 24:18.790
A toast.

24:18.874 --> 24:20.917
To my wonderful husband, Jon.

24:22.419 --> 24:24.504
We're so lucky to have so much.

24:25.547 --> 24:27.966
Let's all reflect for a moment
on our good fortune,

24:28.049 --> 24:32.304
which is so rare
and so precarious in this world.

24:33.388 --> 24:34.347
Cheers.

24:34.890 --> 24:36.474
[all] Cheers.

24:37.976 --> 24:39.311
[crowd] Aww...

24:41.271 --> 24:42.105
Perfect.

24:43.773 --> 24:46.484
Okay, so I have one last surprise.

24:47.152 --> 24:49.112
Hello, my beautiful friends.

24:49.196 --> 24:52.532
I am Ken Yurubi. The Mentalist.

24:52.616 --> 24:54.618
[excited chatter]

24:55.076 --> 24:56.369
Like the TV show?

24:57.120 --> 24:59.581
Well, actually,
<i>The Mentalist</i> was based on me.

24:59.664 --> 25:01.208
Man, you must be loaded!

25:01.291 --> 25:04.085
No, I... No, they didn't...

25:04.169 --> 25:06.213
Forget it. Forget that.

25:06.296 --> 25:10.175
I am here to tell you all
what's in your minds.

25:10.258 --> 25:12.886
[Jon] Ken did a corporate retreat for us
a few months ago

25:12.969 --> 25:15.138
and what he can do, it's just astounding.

25:15.222 --> 25:17.432
No, no. [laughs nervously]

25:17.515 --> 25:18.725
Okay.

25:18.808 --> 25:24.189
Now, folks, I have been watching you
at this little party all night.

25:24.272 --> 25:25.774
[guests groan]

25:25.857 --> 25:28.235
And I just can't wait
to get inside your heads!

25:28.902 --> 25:32.197
Okay. Now, where shall we begin?

25:32.280 --> 25:34.407
[hums indistinctly]

25:34.491 --> 25:35.951
Excuse me,<i> True Blood.</i>

25:36.034 --> 25:37.661
Okay.

25:38.620 --> 25:39.579
-Hi.
-Hi.

25:39.663 --> 25:41.498
-How are you? I'm Ken.
-I'm good.

25:41.581 --> 25:43.166
-Hi, Ken.
-Okay.

25:44.125 --> 25:47.003
You don't tell me who you are. I know.

25:47.087 --> 25:49.589
-Oh.
-Wait. I see a star.

25:51.925 --> 25:53.009
In the night sky.

25:53.593 --> 25:55.595
Star for Stella.<i> Streetcar!</i>

25:55.679 --> 25:57.138
-I was in<i> Streetcar!</i>
-Yes.

25:57.222 --> 25:59.224
-That was my line!
-Yes.

25:59.307 --> 26:01.476
You led him to it.
Marianne, you led him to it.

26:01.559 --> 26:04.145
-This isn't real.
-No, watch. Just watch.

26:04.229 --> 26:06.690
-I see a man.
-Oh, my God, Tag.

26:06.773 --> 26:08.608
-Mm. Mm-hmm.
-[Max] Holy shit.

26:08.692 --> 26:10.735
Guys, nothing is happening.

26:10.819 --> 26:13.029
No, Max, nothing's happening right now.

26:13.113 --> 26:14.948
How does he know everything about Tag?

26:15.031 --> 26:17.325
Did you play the violin as a child?

26:17.409 --> 26:18.618
Yes, I did!

26:18.702 --> 26:19.869
[guests gasp]

26:19.953 --> 26:21.454
-That's what I thought.
-Wow.

26:21.538 --> 26:22.789
You're gay.

26:22.872 --> 26:24.249
[tentative applause]

26:27.460 --> 26:29.921
-[Ethan] Obviously?
-Great accomplishment of mine.

26:30.005 --> 26:31.172
I see a man...

26:32.257 --> 26:33.675
F... F...

26:33.758 --> 26:35.677
-Felix!
-Felix!

26:35.760 --> 26:36.678
-Felix?
-Felix.

26:36.761 --> 26:38.555
-Felix, yeah.
-Felix. Yes.

26:38.638 --> 26:40.640
But Felix isn't, he's not here.

26:40.724 --> 26:42.309
No, and that's sad.

26:42.392 --> 26:44.602
You feel... lonely

26:44.686 --> 26:47.147
and lost at sea.

26:49.983 --> 26:51.609
No, no, no, no. Okay.

26:51.693 --> 26:53.945
Yeah, fine. Thank you.

26:54.029 --> 26:55.530
Come to The Mentalist.

26:55.613 --> 26:57.157
No, I think she needs a hug.

26:57.240 --> 26:58.616
There we go.

26:59.534 --> 27:00.869
She gets a hug.

27:01.369 --> 27:03.997
-Good.
-Why are you clapping?

27:04.080 --> 27:06.291
-Okay.
-Alright, dude.

27:06.374 --> 27:08.793
Can I tell you something about you?
You're in love.

27:09.336 --> 27:10.503
[guests laugh]

27:11.463 --> 27:12.964
Yeah, that's my fiancée.

27:13.882 --> 27:14.758
Not with her.

27:14.841 --> 27:16.009
[guests] Ooh!

27:16.551 --> 27:18.803
Okay, this is not real, so don't worry.

27:20.096 --> 27:23.016
-Tell her it's not real, please.
-I'm not gonna lie to her.

27:23.099 --> 27:26.019
-Tell her it's not real.
-Why would I say that? It's real.

27:26.102 --> 27:27.937
We're all flesh and blood right here.

27:28.021 --> 27:29.314
It's totally fake.

27:29.397 --> 27:31.941
-Okay, no, it's totally real.
-No, it's fake.

27:32.025 --> 27:33.902
No, it's real. Real.

27:34.402 --> 27:35.236
Now...

27:35.945 --> 27:38.907
[Ethan whispers] I do not wanna do this.
I don't even see what the...

27:38.990 --> 27:41.534
And just because of that,
I'm going to you now.

27:41.618 --> 27:45.580
-Don't you think he should be next, folks?
-[guests] Yes!

27:47.082 --> 27:50.835
[in goofy voice] No, no, no, no.
We ain't doing it. Don't do it.

27:50.919 --> 27:54.172
I think someone is nervous
because of the secret.

27:54.255 --> 27:55.131
[Sam gasps]

27:55.215 --> 27:56.466
Oh!

28:00.011 --> 28:01.096
[Ken] Ah!

28:02.514 --> 28:03.348
He!

28:07.519 --> 28:09.020
I had sex with Nick.

28:09.104 --> 28:10.605
[guests gasp]

28:12.107 --> 28:13.400
Oh, my God!

28:13.483 --> 28:15.652
-No. No, mon.
-Whoa!

28:15.735 --> 28:16.736
When?

28:17.987 --> 28:21.783
-Last week in the Caymans.
-[Nick] No. We didn't. It was...

28:21.866 --> 28:23.034
No.

28:23.118 --> 28:25.328
I... I'm so sorry.

28:29.958 --> 28:30.834
Dustry.

28:31.251 --> 28:33.086
This is what happened at the retreat.

28:33.169 --> 28:37.382
Ken just breaks everyone down.
It's just... [sighs]

28:38.383 --> 28:41.803
So then why would you bring him
to my birthday party?

28:41.886 --> 28:43.138
Because I...

28:44.973 --> 28:46.641
I told you I knew how to drive.

28:46.725 --> 28:48.435
Can I try?

28:48.518 --> 28:50.937
No. You're too young. Sorry.

28:51.563 --> 28:54.566
[Pearl gasps] Cake! Come on, cake!

28:55.024 --> 28:56.735
[Pearl and Dash] Cake, cake!

28:56.818 --> 28:58.153
Cake!

28:58.236 --> 28:59.946
-Yeah!
-Cake!

29:01.865 --> 29:04.325
Babe, I'm so sorry.

29:06.035 --> 29:08.872
I love you so much.
I have no idea what happened.

29:09.873 --> 29:11.708
I was out of my mind.

29:11.791 --> 29:14.377
I think... after the wedding, um...

29:15.003 --> 29:16.671
I got crazy and I got paranoid

29:16.755 --> 29:19.966
and I thought something was happening
between you and Sam.

29:20.049 --> 29:22.927
God, I don't know how
you can ever forgive me, but I...

29:24.095 --> 29:25.597
I really hope that you do.

29:25.680 --> 29:27.056
I forgive you.

29:29.809 --> 29:30.643
What?

29:31.144 --> 29:32.729
I said I forgive you.

29:33.271 --> 29:36.483
Um, I love you
and that's all that matters.

29:38.193 --> 29:41.029
You... You forgave me really quickly.

29:41.112 --> 29:43.323
Do you want me to be mad?

29:43.406 --> 29:46.075
[stammers] Would that make it better?

29:47.327 --> 29:48.620
I think it would be better.

29:48.703 --> 29:51.915
I don't think that
I would do something like this

29:51.998 --> 29:55.502
unless I was trying to get
a reaction from you.

29:58.296 --> 30:00.048
Is Sam's car moving?

30:00.965 --> 30:03.343
Sam's car's moving...
Okay, hold on.

30:03.760 --> 30:06.262
Sam? Sam!
I need your car keys right now.

30:06.346 --> 30:09.390
-I don't have them.
-Your car is rolling toward the pool.

30:09.474 --> 30:11.476
What? Oh my, God.

30:11.559 --> 30:13.686
-Oh, my God.
-Do you have keys?

30:13.770 --> 30:16.064
I don't know where the keys are.
Oh, my God!

30:17.774 --> 30:19.567
-Keys are in the car!
-What are we gonna do?

30:19.651 --> 30:20.819
[Sam] We have to stop the car.

30:22.028 --> 30:25.031
-Smash the glass!
-I got the bulletproof glass, we can't.

30:25.114 --> 30:26.574
We're not that important!

30:26.658 --> 30:29.327
-I feel our friendship's in a weird place.
-[shouts] We're fine!

30:29.410 --> 30:32.247
Hey, I should mention to you,
someone in my department

30:32.330 --> 30:35.583
sold a book called<i> Wolf Trials</i>
that I knew about but forgot existed.

30:36.125 --> 30:37.252
[all groan]

30:38.461 --> 30:39.295
Ow!

30:39.379 --> 30:42.048
-My hand!
-You said we were fine!

30:43.383 --> 30:45.301
This thing just broke my foot!

30:45.718 --> 30:46.761
[shrieks]

30:47.679 --> 30:48.888
[Jon] No!

30:52.141 --> 30:53.101
[Ethan] It's going in!

30:55.812 --> 30:57.188
It's going in the pool.

30:58.606 --> 31:00.400
Did you leave it in neutral?

31:00.483 --> 31:02.861
Of course not. I'm not a child.

31:03.236 --> 31:04.070
Oh, no.

31:05.113 --> 31:06.364
Why did you say, "Oh, no"?

31:06.781 --> 31:08.992
In general. Oh, no!

31:10.368 --> 31:12.161
I'm sorry about<i> Wolf Trials.</i>

31:13.413 --> 31:15.665
Well, at least
we still have your income, so...

31:15.748 --> 31:18.376
Oh. Right. I quit.

31:21.087 --> 31:22.088
[Jon] Champagne?

31:22.171 --> 31:23.882
Great. Let's celebrate.

31:25.925 --> 31:31.723
♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪

31:31.806 --> 31:37.353
-♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪
-[laughing]

31:40.773 --> 31:42.650
Sam's car. Had it coming.

31:43.860 --> 31:45.153
[all laugh]

31:46.029 --> 31:47.155
[Lisa] Oh, that's funny.

31:47.822 --> 31:49.198
That's not it.

31:50.533 --> 31:52.452
I think we should take a break.

31:52.911 --> 31:54.829
[soft rock song plays]

32:00.376 --> 32:02.295
[Jon] Oh, right. Fireworks.

32:02.378 --> 32:05.465
That's your last surprise tonight,
sweetie.

32:05.548 --> 32:07.800
Here. [makes pinging sound]
